IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: To positively impact the economic growth of Solano County by maintaining & enhancing a competitive location for businesses to expand & locate, providing direct service to scale local traded sector industries, attracting new jobs & investment, & connecting businesses with resources to meet their needs. The EDC collaborates with the cities, county, workforce development, utilities, & education to deliver all resources.

IRS990.Desc: Solano Business First! is a network of all cities and partner organizations dedicated to reaching out and assisting existing companies in their cities by connecting them with specific resources, information, and services. Resources and services are available to assist businesses with expansions, address economic difficulties, access local, state and federal incentives and with assistance to help the company be more competitive in the broader marketplace.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Confidential Site Location Assistance: Solano EDC works on a confidential basis with companies seeking to identify sites or buildings in the county, provides proposals and data per their request for location-decision evaluation, and will coordinate site tours. Once a company has identified specific sites that meet their needs, the City Economic Development representative will provide primary assistance, with the EDC continuing to provide data on workforce or access to programs to assist with location.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: As a Resource hub, the EDC provides demographic reports for special areas of interest, including information on available workforce, water rates, major employers, and occupations. For companies seeking business financing, the EDC will (1) Make referrals to agencies to assist with loan guarantees, direct financing, SBA loan packages, equipment and real estate financing and Industrial Development Bonds. (2) Assist businesses using recycled materials or diverting materials from the waste stream with Californias Recycling Market Development Zone Loan Program; and (3) Assist with project development infrastructure program financing partnered with a local city.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: This organization made "NO" lobbying or political
There are 7 Levels of Membership: The Legacy Circle, Chair's Circle, Executive Stakeholder, Corporate Investor, Premier Investor, Investor & Non-Profit

Board members are advised before the return is filed that it has been completed and is available for review at the organization's office or online. Board members are encouraged to ask questions, preferably in writing, which are generally answered prior to submitting the return to the IRS.
The Executive Committee and Board Officers establish the salary of the President / CEO during the annual budget process.
The Executive Committee and Board Officers establish the salary of Staff Personnel during the annual budget process.
Documents required by law (Determination Letter, Form 1024 Application, Forms 990) are available at the office upon request by appointment during normal business hours.

None of the Officers or Directors have a Family Relationship. However, some of the Directors have Business Relationships. The Cities of Benicia, Dixon, Fairfield, Rio Vista, Suisun City, Vacaville, Vallejo, and Winters, along with the County of Solano, each have two Directors apiece. Carpenters Local Union, Fairfield-Suisun Sewer District, Kaiser Permanente, and NorthBay Health also have two Directors apiece.
